### SmartAid REST tests — Campaigns CRUD + status transitions
### Note: this is the most logic-heavy area. Status changes move money in/out
### of ngo_accounts and write ledger rows. Open pgAdmin to watch the state.

@host = http://localhost:3000

### Login as admin
# @name login
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@smartaid.com",
  "password": "admin123"
}

### Login as donor (read-only role)
# @name loginDonor
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "donor1@smartaid.com",
  "password": "donor123"
}

### Login as shop_manager
# @name loginManager
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "manager@smartaid.com",
  "password": "manager123"
}

### 1) GET /api/campaigns without token
# Expected: 401
GET {{host}}/api/campaigns

### 2) GET /api/campaigns as shop_manager
# Expected: 403
GET {{host}}/api/campaigns
Authorization: Bearer {{loginManager.response.body.token}}

### 3) GET /api/campaigns as donor (donor IS allowed to read)
# Expected: 200
GET {{host}}/api/campaigns
Authorization: Bearer {{loginDonor.response.body.token}}

### 4) GET /api/campaigns as admin
# Expected: 200
GET {{host}}/api/campaigns
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### 5) POST as donor (donor is read-only)
# Expected: 403
POST {{host}}/api/campaigns
Authorization: Bearer {{loginDonor.response.body.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Should fail",
  "start_date": "2026-06-01",
  "end_date": "2026-06-30",
  "budget": 100
}

### 6) POST missing title
# Expected: 400
POST {{host}}/api/campaigns
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "start_date": "2026-06-01",
  "end_date": "2026-06-30",
  "budget": 100
}

### 7) POST end_date before start_date
# Expected: 400
POST {{host}}/api/campaigns
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Bad dates",
  "start_date": "2026-06-30",
  "end_date": "2026-06-01",
  "budget": 100
}

### 8) POST negative budget
# Expected: 400
POST {{host}}/api/campaigns
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Bad budget",
  "start_date": "2026-06-01",
  "end_date": "2026-06-30",
  "budget": -100
}

### 9) POST valid campaign (small budget so we can activate it)
# Expected: 201, status="draft"
# @name createCampaign
POST {{host}}/api/campaigns
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "REST Test Campaign",
  "location": "Mogadishu",
  "start_date": "2026-06-01",
  "end_date": "2026-06-30",
  "budget": 500
}

### 10) GET single campaign
# Expected: 200
GET {{host}}/api/campaigns/{{createCampaign.response.body.campaign.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### 11) GET non-existent campaign
# Expected: 404
GET {{host}}/api/campaigns/9999
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### 12) Try to skip draft -> closed
# Expected: 409 "Cannot close: campaign is 'draft'"
PUT {{host}}/api/campaigns/{{createCampaign.response.body.campaign.id}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "closed"
}

### 13) Bad status value
# Expected: 400
PUT {{host}}/api/campaigns/{{createCampaign.response.body.campaign.id}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "draft"
}

### 14) Activate the campaign (draft -> active)
# Expected: 200, deducted = 500 from ngo_account, ledger row "campaign_fund"
# Check pgAdmin: ngo_accounts.balance dropped by 500.
PUT {{host}}/api/campaigns/{{createCampaign.response.body.campaign.id}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "active"
}

### 15) Try to activate again (active -> active)
# Expected: 409
PUT {{host}}/api/campaigns/{{createCampaign.response.body.campaign.id}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "active"
}

### 16) Try a budget too big to activate (uses huge budget = 9_999_999)
# Expected: 201 (creation OK) — saves the id for the next request
# @name bigCampaign
POST {{host}}/api/campaigns
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Massive REST Campaign",
  "start_date": "2026-08-01",
  "end_date": "2026-08-31",
  "budget": 9999999
}

### 17) Activate the huge campaign — insufficient NGO balance
# Expected: 409 with details { ngo_balance, campaign_budget }
PUT {{host}}/api/campaigns/{{bigCampaign.response.body.campaign.id}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "active"
}

### 18) Close our REST Test Campaign (active -> closed)
# Expected: 200, refunded = sum of remaining_balance across enrolled beneficiaries
# (Since nothing is enrolled yet, refunded = 0)
# Check pgAdmin: ngo_accounts.balance is back to its pre-activate value.
PUT {{host}}/api/campaigns/{{createCampaign.response.body.campaign.id}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "closed"
}

### 19) Try to close already-closed
# Expected: 409
PUT {{host}}/api/campaigns/{{createCampaign.response.body.campaign.id}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "closed"
}
